# VNC_EC2_Connect
->This is for the information to describe the details about how to connect to remote aws ec2 instance running on Linux or Ubuntu from windows. We use TigerVNC for GUI support to Linux or Ubuntu running over ec2 instances.

#Problem
->Window with low resources and want to use cloud provider resources and not able to use because of CLI interface. 

#Objective
->To use the resources of aws ec2 having linux or ubuntu install through GUI with help of TigerVNC Viewer.

#Set Up Procedure
Connecting to remote aws EC2 Instance using PuTTy or PowerShell over SSH.
- Start a new session with Host/IP Address(Publis) i.e username@public_ip_address, mention port - 22, Connection Type - SSH, provide a name to Session.
  Go to SSH under Connection from Category then click Auth>Credentials, here you have to provide .ppk(Putty Private Key) which is transformed from .pem(privacy enhanced        mail). Use online service to convert .pem to .ppk or use puttygen to download the .ppk file. Use this .ppk file to upload to Private Key for Authentication using Browse      and save    the session from session category.
- you will be login to ec2 instance here you have to install 2 dependency to connect with TigerVNC, Use this below command to install xfce4 and vnc server.
  sudo apt update
  sudo apt install xfce4 xfce4-goodies tigervnc-standalone-server -y
- change the password of vnc server which will be asked while connecting to it through TigerVNC viewer. user below command.
  vncpasswd
- Create or edit xstartup file under .vnc to launch your desktop environment when the VNC server starts with below details.
 ~/.vnc/xstartup
  #!/bin/bash
  unset SESSION_MANAGER
  unset DBUS_SESSION_BUS_ADDRESS
  exec startxfce4
- Once above step completed use below command to start server with profile :1
  vncserver :1
- we have to map it to localhost you can use below command or set up in Putty.
  ssh -i your-key.pem -L 5901:localhost:5901 ubuntu@your-ec2-ip
  for PuTTY go to Auth>Tunnel section under SSH, mention source port - 5901 and destination to localhost:5901 and click add to add these to tunnel and save to session under
  session category.
- once every setup is completed use TigerVNC to connect with address localhost:5901 and provide the password that you set up earlier with vncpasswd.

